Baby penguins waddles their way into adulthood after graduating from "Fish School". The penguins are taught to eat from the zookeeper's hands, to make sure they get the right nutrients. They also learn to become comfortable around people. Same-sex penguin couple become best daddies at SF Zoo Two male penguins are setting relationship goals since 2015 at the San Francisco Zoo in the USA after successfully raising three chicks and becoming the go-to daddies with their unique ability to incubate, foster and care for the little ones.